12
00:01:11,446 --> 00:01:14,950
♪ Lupin the Third ♪

13
00:01:14,950 --> 00:01:18,620
♪

14
00:01:25,043 --> 00:01:35,262
♪

15
00:01:35,262 --> 00:01:38,390
(whistling)

16
00:01:38,390 --> 00:01:48,734
♪

17
00:01:48,734 --> 00:01:50,736
I'm the only one with
a reason to be happy!

18
00:01:50,736 --> 00:01:52,112
Knock it off!

19
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:54,197
And I am pretty darn happy.

20
00:01:54,197 --> 00:01:56,033
(laughing)

21
00:01:56,033 --> 00:01:57,743
Good, we'll toast
to your success

22
00:01:57,743 --> 00:01:59,411
once we get back home to Japan.

23
00:01:59,411 --> 00:02:00,454
That's right,

24
00:02:00,454 --> 00:02:02,748
and I'm gonna spring
for the best one they got!

25
00:02:02,748 --> 00:02:06,501
(slurping)

26
00:02:06,501 --> 00:02:08,879
Hmm‐‐what the hell's that?

27
00:02:08,879 --> 00:02:16,428
♪

28
00:02:16,428 --> 00:02:19,264
What's going on here?

29
00:02:19,264 --> 00:02:21,558
Look, whatever it is, we‐‐

30
00:02:21,558 --> 00:02:25,395
♪

31
00:02:25,395 --> 00:02:28,023
(hissing)

32
00:02:28,023 --> 00:02:29,608
All right, guys,
let's break it up!

33
00:02:29,608 --> 00:02:31,443
Clear the road!

34
00:02:31,443 --> 00:02:34,237
(zapping)

35
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:36,323
(screaming)

36
00:02:38,533 --> 00:02:41,203
(groaning)

37
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:58,845
(grunting)

38
00:03:02,265 --> 00:03:04,685
(yelling)

39
00:03:06,728 --> 00:03:08,313
What the freakin' hell?

40
00:03:08,313 --> 00:03:10,023
Suicide beams!

41
00:03:10,023 --> 00:03:14,403
♪

42
00:03:14,403 --> 00:03:16,613
(panting)

43
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:39,719
♪

44
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:41,888
(clacking)

45
00:03:41,888 --> 00:03:45,016
♪

46
00:03:46,184 --> 00:03:47,936
What do you mean you're
not gonna get involved?

47
00:03:47,936 --> 00:03:49,896
You're the Chief of
Police, for Pete's sake!

48
00:03:49,896 --> 00:03:51,523
And the victims were your men!

49
00:03:51,523 --> 00:03:53,525
It sounds like the
work of the Basala Army.

50
00:03:53,525 --> 00:03:56,194
I wouldn't wanna tangle
with them if I were you!

51
00:03:56,194 --> 00:03:57,529
Basala Army?

52
00:03:57,529 --> 00:03:59,030
The Basala Army are thugs

53
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:00,824
who have the whole of
India living in fear.

54
00:04:00,824 --> 00:04:03,618
Just a single shot from
one of their suicide beams,

55
00:04:03,618 --> 00:04:05,245
and it's all over.

56
00:04:05,245 --> 00:04:08,290
‐If they have Lupin‐‐
‐Well, stop 'em then!

57
00:04:08,290 --> 00:04:11,543
If Lupin dies, my whole
life's over with, you hear?

58
00:04:11,543 --> 00:04:14,629
And if you won't help, then
I'll just go after him alone!

59
00:04:14,629 --> 00:04:16,423
But really, my dear
Inspector Zenigata,

60
00:04:16,423 --> 00:04:17,883
you must think about this:

61
00:04:17,883 --> 00:04:20,343
If your aim was this far
off shooting at your own head,

62
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:23,638
how in the world do you
expect to hit any of them, eh?

63
00:04:23,638 --> 00:04:25,724
(groaning)

64
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:32,063
I see you're a
boxers man, Mr. Lupin.

65
00:04:32,063 --> 00:04:35,942
Well, if it isn't the Suicide
King himself, Basala Lavahna.

66
00:04:35,942 --> 00:04:37,027
That right?

67
00:04:37,027 --> 00:04:38,904
Hmm, how do you know me?

68
00:04:38,904 --> 00:04:41,573
You're too humble‐‐you,
sir, are a very famous man,

69
00:04:41,573 --> 00:04:44,034
although I suppose "notorious"
would be a better word

70
00:04:44,034 --> 00:04:46,870
for a crackpot scientist
turned murderous gangster.

71
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:48,413
(grumbling)

72
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:50,540
Hey, watch your mouth, you!

73
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:52,501
All right, what do
you want, Basala?

74
00:04:52,501 --> 00:04:55,462
You stole 20,000 diamonds and
hid them somewhere in India.

75
00:04:55,462 --> 00:04:57,214
I want you to tell
me where they are.

76
00:04:57,214 --> 00:04:59,925
Jigen, what the hell
is he talking about?

77
00:04:59,925 --> 00:05:02,260
Hmm, you got me.

78
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:04,846
We can do this easy,

79
00:05:04,846 --> 00:05:07,641
or we can do it hard.

80
00:05:07,641 --> 00:05:09,559
(groaning)

81
00:05:09,559 --> 00:05:13,146
All right, all right, let go!

82
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:16,399
Very good, now talk!

83
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:18,401
Where are the diamonds?

84
00:05:21,947 --> 00:05:24,574
♪

85
00:05:24,574 --> 00:05:26,785
Now unless you want a
complimentary tracheotomy,

86
00:05:26,785 --> 00:05:28,912
you're gonna let us go.

87
00:05:28,912 --> 00:05:30,455
You really wanna see
if one of your bullets

88
00:05:30,455 --> 00:05:32,249
is faster than this knife?

89
00:05:32,249 --> 00:05:34,459
Wait, hold on‐‐I‐‐I‐‐I‐‐

90
00:05:34,459 --> 00:05:36,837
All right, sunshine,
get over here.

91
00:05:36,837 --> 00:05:41,007
♪

92
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:43,301
How do you like my
boxers now, Basala?

93
00:05:43,301 --> 00:05:45,011
Not as much now.

94
00:05:46,638 --> 00:05:49,891
(yelling)

95
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:52,477
Apparently you will
acquire another demonstration

96
00:05:52,477 --> 00:05:54,396
of my suicide beam!

97
00:05:54,396 --> 00:06:03,780
♪

98
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:04,990
How's that old joke go?

99
00:06:04,990 --> 00:06:07,993
"I went hunting for an
elephant in my boxers"?

100
00:06:07,993 --> 00:06:10,871
(zapping)

101
00:06:10,871 --> 00:06:13,164
(trumpeting)

102
00:06:19,546 --> 00:06:21,506
Maybe he didn't like the joke.

103
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:24,718
Nobody likes that joke.

104
00:06:24,718 --> 00:06:27,846
Tell me where they are,
and I'll switch it off!

105
00:06:27,846 --> 00:06:28,972
Hey, you want diamonds?

106
00:06:28,972 --> 00:06:31,349
Here's a crazy thought,
go to a jewelry store!

107
00:06:31,349 --> 00:06:35,020
I cannot tell if you are
courageous or just an idiot.

108
00:06:35,020 --> 00:06:37,147
Maybe this will help.

109
00:06:37,147 --> 00:06:39,983
(buzzing)

110
00:06:46,197 --> 00:06:48,408
In any case, it comes
down to the same thing.

111
00:06:48,408 --> 00:06:51,870
You either talk or you die.

112
00:06:51,870 --> 00:06:54,831
(grunting)

113
00:06:54,831 --> 00:06:59,210
♪

114
00:06:59,210 --> 00:07:00,295
You comfy?

115
00:07:00,295 --> 00:07:02,505
You know, something
just doesn't add up.

116
00:07:02,505 --> 00:07:04,466
‐Go on.
‐You and me and Goemon

117
00:07:04,466 --> 00:07:06,426
were the only three
people in the whole world

118
00:07:06,426 --> 00:07:07,552
who knew about these diamonds,

119
00:07:07,552 --> 00:07:09,888
so how the hell did
Basala get tipped off?

120
00:07:09,888 --> 00:07:12,223
Hint‐‐it starts with an F.

121
00:07:12,223 --> 00:07:13,725
Fujiko?

122
00:07:13,725 --> 00:07:16,186
I'll bet she's in it
with the Basala Army

123
00:07:16,186 --> 00:07:17,896
up to her cleavage!

124
00:07:17,896 --> 00:07:19,731
Jigen, you've got it all wrong!

125
00:07:19,731 --> 00:07:20,732
I'm‐‐

126
00:07:20,732 --> 00:07:23,026
(whimpering)

127
00:07:24,694 --> 00:07:27,614
This is getting old real fast.

128
00:07:27,614 --> 00:07:29,491
Let's call 911.

129
00:07:31,701 --> 00:07:32,744
Hey, Goemon!

130
00:07:32,744 --> 00:07:34,079
Lupin to Goemon!

131
00:07:34,079 --> 00:07:40,126
♪

132
00:07:40,126 --> 00:07:41,753
Goemon, please, come in!

133
00:07:41,753 --> 00:07:43,838
S. O. S., S. O. S.!

134
00:07:43,838 --> 00:07:46,591
Dammit, he's probably
meditating or something.

135
00:07:46,591 --> 00:07:50,762
Oh, please, Goemon, please,
snap out of it, will ya?

136
00:07:50,762 --> 00:07:54,557
Well, at least one of
us is perfectly serene.

137
00:07:54,557 --> 00:07:57,394
I can't hold on.

138
00:07:57,394 --> 00:07:59,187
Don't jostle me
if you wuss out.

139
00:07:59,187 --> 00:08:00,772
I'm holding up pretty good here.

140
00:08:00,772 --> 00:08:03,274
You thought the
elephant joke bit!

141
00:08:07,195 --> 00:08:08,697
What the‐‐

142
00:08:08,697 --> 00:08:09,656
Huh?

143
00:08:09,656 --> 00:08:12,951
I know, I know, how
can you ever thank me?

144
00:08:12,951 --> 00:08:16,955
Well, cash is always welcome.

145
00:08:16,955 --> 00:08:19,290
That's my Fuji‐cakes!

146
00:08:19,290 --> 00:08:20,959
Fujiko, you're a guardian angel!

147
00:08:20,959 --> 00:08:22,669
We were done for!

148
00:08:27,173 --> 00:08:29,467
‐Come on!
‐See, what'd I tell ya?

149
00:08:29,467 --> 00:08:31,511
She's totally on our side.

150
00:08:31,511 --> 00:08:33,972
‐Yeah, we'll see.
‐Hmph.

151
00:08:36,307 --> 00:08:50,530
♪

152
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:51,990
Hey, look at that!

153
00:08:51,990 --> 00:08:53,867
Yup, the Taj Mahal!

154
00:08:53,867 --> 00:08:56,703
♪

155
00:08:56,703 --> 00:08:58,413
You think the locals
might be a little shocked

156
00:08:58,413 --> 00:09:01,332
to find out this
is Basala's hideout?

157
00:09:01,332 --> 00:09:02,584
By the way, Fuji‐cakes,

158
00:09:02,584 --> 00:09:04,419
I'm impressed that you found us.

159
00:09:04,419 --> 00:09:06,254
Well, thanks to this.

160
00:09:06,254 --> 00:09:08,339
I just happened to be
here doing some sightseeing

161
00:09:08,339 --> 00:09:10,175
when I heard your
S. O. S. to Goemon.

162
00:09:10,175 --> 00:09:12,635
You guys happen to
be incredibly lucky.

163
00:09:12,635 --> 00:09:14,804
Yeah, well, not anymore.

164
00:09:16,765 --> 00:09:18,933
‐Let's go!
‐Get them!

165
00:09:20,643 --> 00:09:30,111
♪

166
00:09:30,111 --> 00:09:32,113
Damn, where did they go?

167
00:09:32,113 --> 00:09:34,741
♪

168
00:09:34,741 --> 00:09:36,993
All right, everybody get out.

169
00:09:36,993 --> 00:09:39,537
♪

170
00:09:39,537 --> 00:09:41,081
They're hiding somewhere
in here, I know it.

171
00:09:41,081 --> 00:09:43,416
Go ahead and kill
the whole herd!

172
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:44,501
We cannot do that.

173
00:09:44,501 --> 00:09:47,128
‐It would be a big sin.
‐Very bad karma.

174
00:09:47,128 --> 00:09:49,506
What are you damn
fools waiting for?

175
00:09:49,506 --> 00:09:52,509
These cows are very
sacred animals to us.

176
00:09:52,509 --> 00:09:53,718
Fairy tales!

177
00:09:53,718 --> 00:09:56,346
I order you to
slaughter this herd!

178
00:09:56,346 --> 00:09:58,098
Whoa there, easy now.

179
00:09:58,098 --> 00:09:59,599
Just about there.

180
00:10:01,309 --> 00:10:02,727
Superstitious idiots.

181
00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:05,688
All right, I'll just do
it myself if I have to.

182
00:10:05,688 --> 00:10:08,274
(motor rumbling)

183
00:10:08,274 --> 00:10:09,609
Damn!

184
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:12,529
♪

185
00:10:12,529 --> 00:10:13,905
After them!

186
00:10:13,905 --> 00:10:15,907
They're getting away!

187
00:10:15,907 --> 00:10:28,545
♪

188
00:10:28,545 --> 00:10:29,546
What's up?

189
00:10:29,546 --> 00:10:30,588
You're kinda quiet.

190
00:10:30,588 --> 00:10:32,674
I, um, was just
wondering if you were ever

191
00:10:32,674 --> 00:10:36,469
planning on telling me
about all those diamonds.

192
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:37,887
What are you talking about?

193
00:10:37,887 --> 00:10:40,640
I overheard them talking about
it when I ran to your rescue,

194
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:43,059
so don't you try and pull
your innocent act with me,

195
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:45,812
you greedy, ungrateful,
rotten son of a bitch!

196
00:10:45,812 --> 00:10:47,105
Where the hell are they?

197
00:10:47,105 --> 00:10:48,273
Don't fall for it.

198
00:10:48,273 --> 00:10:50,859
She has a very nasty habit
of betraying us, Lupin.

199
00:10:50,859 --> 00:10:51,985
That is so unfair!

200
00:10:51,985 --> 00:10:53,111
I've turned over a new leaf!

201
00:10:53,111 --> 00:10:55,864
I did risk my life
to save you, after all.

202
00:10:55,864 --> 00:10:58,283
♪

203
00:10:58,283 --> 00:11:00,618
So that's how you
wanna play it, huh?

204
00:11:03,746 --> 00:11:06,291
Lupin, even if you were
the last man on Earth

205
00:11:06,291 --> 00:11:07,500
and I was the last woman,

206
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,794
I could never love you
after this, you hear?

207
00:11:09,794 --> 00:11:10,753
Never!

208
00:11:10,753 --> 00:11:12,338
That's the last straw‐‐goodbye.

209
00:11:12,338 --> 00:11:14,340
Fujiko, no, wait, hold on!

210
00:11:14,340 --> 00:11:15,300
Come on!

211
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:17,177
Come on, let's not be so hasty!

212
00:11:17,177 --> 00:11:20,138
Oh, Lupin, I love
it when you trust me.

213
00:11:20,138 --> 00:11:21,723
Really?

214
00:11:21,723 --> 00:11:23,641
(giggling)

215
00:11:23,641 --> 00:11:25,768
The diamonds are in Kolkata.

216
00:11:25,768 --> 00:11:26,686
Really?

217
00:11:26,686 --> 00:11:28,605
And where exactly in
Kolkata would they be?

218
00:11:28,605 --> 00:11:31,482
It's a classic case of
hiding in plain sight.

219
00:11:31,482 --> 00:11:32,817
In fact, all you have to do is‐‐

220
00:11:32,817 --> 00:11:34,485
Can't you see what
she's doing, man?

221
00:11:34,485 --> 00:11:36,196
She's got you
wrapped around her!

222
00:11:36,196 --> 00:11:38,031
You stay out of this!

223
00:11:38,031 --> 00:11:39,365
No way!

224
00:11:39,365 --> 00:11:41,784
(grunting)

225
00:11:41,784 --> 00:11:43,286
‐Damn, it's a sinkhole!
‐Ah, help!

226
00:11:43,286 --> 00:11:44,704
Fujiko, help us!

227
00:11:44,704 --> 00:11:45,997
Lupin!

228
00:11:45,997 --> 00:11:48,166
(panting)

229
00:11:48,166 --> 00:11:51,211
♪

230
00:11:51,211 --> 00:11:52,921
♪ Lupin the Third ♪

231
00:11:58,259 --> 00:12:00,303
♪ Lupin the Third ♪

232
00:12:02,096 --> 00:12:04,140
Lupin, oh my God, no!

233
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:06,351
Lupin, Jigen!

234
00:12:06,351 --> 00:12:08,269
(crying)

235
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:10,772
Why all the tears, my dear?

236
00:12:10,772 --> 00:12:11,898
It's this sinkhole!

237
00:12:11,898 --> 00:12:13,399
It just swallowed them both up!

238
00:12:13,399 --> 00:12:15,318
Please, you've got to save them!

239
00:12:15,318 --> 00:12:17,195
It's too late, my dear.

240
00:12:17,195 --> 00:12:19,614
Did you happen to make
any progress with them?

241
00:12:19,614 --> 00:12:21,074
That's cold.

242
00:12:21,074 --> 00:12:23,034
Our understanding was
that you would find out

243
00:12:23,034 --> 00:12:25,036
where the stones are hidden.

244
00:12:26,913 --> 00:12:29,540
All he said was the
diamonds are in Mumbai.

245
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:30,583
Mumbai?

246
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:33,169
He was just about to tell
me more when he fell in.

247
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:35,964
Very well‐‐that is actually
more help than you realize.

248
00:12:35,964 --> 00:12:37,715
I suggest we leave immediately.

249
00:12:37,715 --> 00:12:39,884
‐I'm out of this.
‐The diamonds have suddenly

250
00:12:39,884 --> 00:12:41,302
lost their luster for you?

251
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:43,596
I guess I'm not as
cold‐hearted as you.

252
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:45,306
It's a tainted legacy now.

253
00:12:45,306 --> 00:12:46,557
Very honorable‐‐just make sure

254
00:12:46,557 --> 00:12:48,518
you do not whine about it later.

255
00:12:48,518 --> 00:12:49,852
Go!

256
00:12:49,852 --> 00:12:51,771
♪

257
00:12:51,771 --> 00:12:53,690
Something smells here.

258
00:12:53,690 --> 00:12:56,150
No woman would ever
pass up diamonds.

259
00:12:56,150 --> 00:13:03,950
♪

260
00:13:03,950 --> 00:13:05,743
I'll come back here
and spread diamonds

261
00:13:05,743 --> 00:13:08,496
all around in your
memory, Lupin, how's that?

262
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:10,832
Bye‐bye!

263
00:13:10,832 --> 00:13:13,167
(engine starting)

264
00:13:15,837 --> 00:13:17,880
(yelling)

265
00:13:20,091 --> 00:13:21,676
Yeah, what'd I tell ya, Lupin?

266
00:13:21,676 --> 00:13:22,760
We put on a little charade

267
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:26,431
and that bitch exposes
herself for exactly what she is.

268
00:13:26,431 --> 00:13:27,598
Damn, that's it.

269
00:13:27,598 --> 00:13:30,435
I'm never‐‐huh?

270
00:13:30,435 --> 00:13:32,353
Jigen, over there!

271
00:13:32,353 --> 00:13:34,731
What the hell is that?

272
00:13:34,731 --> 00:13:37,025
♪

273
00:13:37,025 --> 00:13:38,943
Well, it looks like
our friend Basala

274
00:13:38,943 --> 00:13:40,611
is off on a treasure hunt.

275
00:13:40,611 --> 00:13:42,572
That means Fujiko's in danger!

276
00:13:42,572 --> 00:13:43,781
‐I‐‐
‐I thought you said

277
00:13:43,781 --> 00:13:46,242
you were finished with her!

278
00:13:46,242 --> 00:13:47,410
Look, I know she's no good,

279
00:13:47,410 --> 00:13:49,495
but that doesn't
matter‐‐I love her!

280
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:54,125
♪

281
00:13:54,125 --> 00:13:55,126
That damn woman!

282
00:13:55,126 --> 00:13:57,128
That is the road to Kolkata!

283
00:13:57,128 --> 00:14:13,436
♪

284
00:14:13,436 --> 00:14:15,396
Could all of you please
get out of my way?

285
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:16,481
Now?

286
00:14:16,481 --> 00:14:19,317
"In plain sight"‐‐
those were his words.

287
00:14:21,986 --> 00:14:24,989
How can we search for
anything, let alone diamonds,

288
00:14:24,989 --> 00:14:25,990
when it's so crowded?

289
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:27,158
You have to learn to be patient

290
00:14:27,158 --> 00:14:29,202
and to bide your time
in these circumstances.

291
00:14:29,202 --> 00:14:32,455
Meanwhile, it is very nearly
bathing time in the Ganges.

292
00:14:32,455 --> 00:14:34,207
I have an idea.

293
00:14:34,207 --> 00:14:40,588
♪

294
00:14:40,588 --> 00:14:42,423
What part of "get
the hell out of my way"

295
00:14:42,423 --> 00:14:44,509
don't you understand?

296
00:14:46,344 --> 00:14:48,054
It's Basala!

297
00:14:48,054 --> 00:14:58,689
♪

298
00:14:58,689 --> 00:15:01,442
Just keep your eyes on
her until she kills herself.

299
00:15:04,946 --> 00:15:17,041
♪

300
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:20,253
(engine rumbling)

301
00:15:20,253 --> 00:15:22,088
♪

302
00:15:22,088 --> 00:15:24,215
Listen, I want you to
dig up all of Kolkata

303
00:15:24,215 --> 00:15:25,591
if you have to‐‐understand?

304
00:15:25,591 --> 00:15:26,801
Now, go!

305
00:15:26,801 --> 00:15:30,096
(rumbling)

306
00:15:30,096 --> 00:15:32,390
(shattering)

307
00:15:35,059 --> 00:15:36,811
Hey, Fujiko!

308
00:15:36,811 --> 00:15:38,646
Hey!

309
00:15:38,646 --> 00:15:40,189
♪ Lupe ♪

310
00:15:40,189 --> 00:15:42,191
What the‐‐hey!

311
00:15:43,693 --> 00:15:44,944
Ah!

312
00:15:44,944 --> 00:15:47,280
♪

313
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:48,406
♪ Lupe ♪

314
00:15:48,406 --> 00:15:50,533
♪ Lupin the Third ♪

315
00:15:50,533 --> 00:15:52,535
‐Mhm?
‐Boss, Lupin is here!

316
00:15:52,535 --> 00:15:56,455
Yes, well then, I've
got a surprise for him!

317
00:15:56,455 --> 00:15:58,166
I want her alive.

318
00:15:58,166 --> 00:16:03,838
♪

319
00:16:03,838 --> 00:16:07,175
♪ Lupin the Third ♪

320
00:16:07,175 --> 00:16:10,636
♪ Lupin the Third ♪

321
00:16:10,636 --> 00:16:14,056
♪

322
00:16:14,056 --> 00:16:15,516
Hey, Fujiko!

323
00:16:15,516 --> 00:16:18,311
I love the color
of potassium cyanide!

324
00:16:18,311 --> 00:16:20,146
Potassium cyanide?

325
00:16:20,146 --> 00:16:22,064
It looks so tasty.

326
00:16:24,734 --> 00:16:25,735
No!

327
00:16:25,735 --> 00:16:28,613
Don't, Fujiko!

328
00:16:28,613 --> 00:16:30,198
Fujiko!

329
00:16:33,159 --> 00:16:36,954
♪

330
00:16:36,954 --> 00:16:39,999
I'm afraid you've been
snookered, Mr. Lupin!

331
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:43,294
That was a deathly
bomb of suicide beams.

332
00:16:43,294 --> 00:16:46,756
Your friend, Miss
Fujiko, is over there.

333
00:16:46,756 --> 00:16:49,926
Fujiko!

334
00:16:49,926 --> 00:16:53,012
I furnished her with the
antidote to the suicide ray.

335
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:57,475
Now you are infected
with it, my pesky friend.

336
00:16:57,475 --> 00:16:59,185
It's too late, Mr. Lupin.

337
00:16:59,185 --> 00:17:01,604
Why don't you take aim at
your own head, my friend?

338
00:17:01,604 --> 00:17:03,105
Go on!

339
00:17:03,105 --> 00:17:10,738
♪

340
00:17:10,738 --> 00:17:12,490
(gun shot)

341
00:17:17,620 --> 00:17:19,247
What the hell are you doing?

342
00:17:19,247 --> 00:17:21,457
Oh, just trying to off myself.

343
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:23,167
Seriously, what's up?

344
00:17:23,167 --> 00:17:24,835
I'm off to the afterlife.

345
00:17:24,835 --> 00:17:26,170
See ya!

346
00:17:26,170 --> 00:17:29,382
Wait, Lupin, hey!

347
00:17:29,382 --> 00:17:31,717
(chuckling)

348
00:17:31,717 --> 00:17:34,512
(grunting)

349
00:17:34,512 --> 00:17:36,806
Oh, look at them!

350
00:17:37,682 --> 00:17:39,016
(buzzing)

351
00:17:39,016 --> 00:17:40,434
Sir, we found the diamonds!

352
00:17:40,434 --> 00:17:42,687
‐Good, where?
‐The Yoga Center!

353
00:17:42,687 --> 00:17:45,565
Stay right there‐‐
I am on my way!

354
00:17:45,565 --> 00:17:48,109
(grunting)

355
00:17:48,109 --> 00:17:56,075
♪

356
00:17:56,075 --> 00:17:57,910
Move, you bastard!

357
00:17:57,910 --> 00:18:00,204
(groaning)

358
00:18:00,204 --> 00:18:02,623
So, what is this?

359
00:18:02,623 --> 00:18:04,625
This crazy person is just
sitting on the diamonds!

360
00:18:04,625 --> 00:18:06,043
We can't get him off, Sayeb!

361
00:18:06,043 --> 00:18:07,128
Get away!

362
00:18:07,128 --> 00:18:09,463
‐Fire a suicide blast at him!
‐Right!

363
00:18:09,463 --> 00:18:10,923
Now!

364
00:18:10,923 --> 00:18:13,301
(buzzing)

365
00:18:15,052 --> 00:18:18,264
Dammit, he has obtained a
state of perfect equilibrium.

366
00:18:18,264 --> 00:18:19,890
The beam cannot effect him.

367
00:18:19,890 --> 00:18:21,767
Into the gondola right now!

368
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:26,355
♪

369
00:18:26,355 --> 00:18:27,565
♪ I can't wait to die ♪

370
00:18:27,565 --> 00:18:28,899
♪ It's so nice to die ♪

371
00:18:28,899 --> 00:18:30,651
♪ Happy guy, la‐la‐la ♪

372
00:18:30,651 --> 00:18:32,236
Lupin, quit movin', will ya?

373
00:18:32,236 --> 00:18:33,487
You're gonna‐‐

374
00:18:33,487 --> 00:18:35,448
Wee!

375
00:18:38,034 --> 00:18:40,828
(grunting)

376
00:18:40,828 --> 00:18:42,788
Yeesh, that sure
was a close one.

377
00:18:42,788 --> 00:18:44,290
Lupin!

378
00:18:44,290 --> 00:18:45,583
This rope's for you.

379
00:18:45,583 --> 00:18:47,835
Don't move a single muscle.

380
00:18:47,835 --> 00:18:50,254
A rope, that's cool!

381
00:18:50,254 --> 00:18:51,547
Please, can I have it?

382
00:18:51,547 --> 00:18:53,174
You're just surrendering?

383
00:18:53,174 --> 00:18:55,259
Uh, here‐‐

384
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:57,511
I'm gonna die!

385
00:18:57,511 --> 00:18:59,889
Wha‐‐what the hell is going on?

386
00:18:59,889 --> 00:19:01,474
Hey!

387
00:19:01,474 --> 00:19:03,684
(yelling)

388
00:19:05,561 --> 00:19:06,812
Hmm, that's bizarre.

389
00:19:06,812 --> 00:19:08,522
It's like all of a
sudden I don't even

390
00:19:08,522 --> 00:19:10,066
wanna go on living anymore.

391
00:19:10,066 --> 00:19:12,360
Yeah, what's the point in
just chasing after Lupin

392
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:14,278
and never catching
him year after year?

393
00:19:14,278 --> 00:19:15,946
There is no point!

394
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:20,951
What the hell's going on?

395
00:19:20,951 --> 00:19:22,119
Can't you tell?

396
00:19:22,119 --> 00:19:24,121
It is contagious!

397
00:19:24,121 --> 00:19:25,873
Come on, we all
gotta go sometime!

398
00:19:25,873 --> 00:19:27,458
What do you say we
go together, huh?

399
00:19:27,458 --> 00:19:29,877
‐Come on, Jigen.
‐Thanks, but no thanks.

400
00:19:29,877 --> 00:19:34,507
♪

401
00:19:34,507 --> 00:19:36,509
He'll be waking up soon.

402
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:43,974
(yawning)

403
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:50,022
(groaning)

404
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:52,858
(yelling)

405
00:19:52,858 --> 00:19:55,736
♪

406
00:19:55,736 --> 00:19:57,113
Oh, my golly, no!

407
00:19:57,113 --> 00:19:59,448
Forget him‐‐the diamonds are
the only thing that matters.

408
00:19:59,448 --> 00:20:01,033
Now, open the trunk!

409
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:06,831
♪

410
00:20:06,831 --> 00:20:08,624
‐Ahh!
‐What‐‐what is it?

411
00:20:08,624 --> 00:20:10,960
Oh, it's cow dung!

412
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:12,837
Cow dung?

413
00:20:12,837 --> 00:20:15,506
Don't just stand
there, get rid of it!

414
00:20:15,506 --> 00:20:22,346
♪

415
00:20:22,346 --> 00:20:24,598
There, now try to kill yourself!

416
00:20:24,598 --> 00:20:26,851
Hey, I could bleed to death
if I could bite my tongue!

417
00:20:26,851 --> 00:20:29,937
Hey, hey, hey, stop
it, you damn maniac!

418
00:20:29,937 --> 00:20:34,817
Hey, Goemon, you got anything
you can shove into his mouth?

419
00:20:34,817 --> 00:20:37,111
Um, this might do
the trick for now.

420
00:20:37,111 --> 00:20:39,155
Ah, perfect.

421
00:20:41,449 --> 00:20:44,660
Man, I've wanted to do
that for a long time.

422
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:48,414
♪

423
00:20:48,414 --> 00:20:49,874
Huh‐‐either he's bought it,

424
00:20:49,874 --> 00:20:51,208
or that crap cured him!

425
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:54,879
Hmm, perhaps it's karmic
repayment for mad cow disease.

426
00:20:54,879 --> 00:20:56,922
Hey, guys, what's going on?

427
00:20:56,922 --> 00:20:58,424
You know, I just ate something,

428
00:20:58,424 --> 00:21:00,676
but I can't exactly
remember what it was.

429
00:21:00,676 --> 00:21:03,053
Hmm, it was from a cow.

430
00:21:03,053 --> 00:21:04,889
Ah, yeah.

431
00:21:04,889 --> 00:21:06,557
Some kind of local burger, huh?

432
00:21:06,557 --> 00:21:07,975
It was great.

433
00:21:07,975 --> 00:21:08,934
Huh?

434
00:21:08,934 --> 00:21:11,270
Basala, he's
getting away, come on!

435
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:15,399
No one humiliates
the Basala Army!

436
00:21:15,399 --> 00:21:17,443
(buzzing)

437
00:21:17,443 --> 00:21:20,488
♪

438
00:21:22,406 --> 00:21:25,993
♪

439
00:21:25,993 --> 00:21:27,703
What the hell happened to me?

440
00:21:27,703 --> 00:21:29,497
Hey, wait a minute.

441
00:21:29,497 --> 00:21:31,749
There's another hole!

442
00:21:31,749 --> 00:21:34,126
Now, I wonder
how that got there.

443
00:21:34,126 --> 00:21:35,127
♪ Lupe ♪

444
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:37,421
♪ Lupin the Third ♪

445
00:21:37,421 --> 00:21:40,716
♪

446
00:21:40,716 --> 00:21:43,177
Okay, steady...

447
00:21:43,177 --> 00:21:45,721
and light it!

448
00:21:45,721 --> 00:21:52,019
♪

449
00:21:52,019 --> 00:21:53,103
Ahh!

450
00:21:53,103 --> 00:21:54,980
Oh, this is very bad.

451
00:21:54,980 --> 00:21:58,901
♪

452
00:22:08,994 --> 00:22:10,454
Hey, Lupin, you lied to me.

453
00:22:10,454 --> 00:22:12,915
Why did you say the
diamonds were in Kolkata?

454
00:22:12,915 --> 00:22:15,876
I didn't lie, they're in
plain view, just like I said.

455
00:22:15,876 --> 00:22:18,879
Then I'm gonna laugh last.

456
00:22:18,879 --> 00:22:20,923
♪

457
00:22:20,923 --> 00:22:22,299
You'll see!

458
00:22:22,299 --> 00:22:24,802
Obsession, thy name is Woman.

459
00:22:24,802 --> 00:22:28,347
I'm not sure she'd still
want 'em if she did find 'em.

460
00:22:28,347 --> 00:22:31,183
Shh, keep it down.

461
00:22:31,183 --> 00:22:36,438
♪

462
00:22:36,438 --> 00:22:38,691
20,000 cows, one diamond each.

463
00:22:38,691 --> 00:22:40,067
Safest place in all of India

464
00:22:40,067 --> 00:22:41,443
if you're looking
to hide something.

465
00:22:41,443 --> 00:22:44,071
It might not be real
pretty when it comes out,

466
00:22:44,071 --> 00:22:45,573
but the great
thing about diamonds

467
00:22:45,573 --> 00:22:47,950
is they clean up real nice.

468
00:22:47,950 --> 00:22:52,663
♪

469
00:22:52,663 --> 00:22:56,125
(horn blowing)

470
00:22:56,125 --> 00:22:58,168
See you holy
heifers in Yokohama!

471
00:22:58,168 --> 00:23:00,296
We'll set you all up
on a nice farm somewhere

472
00:23:00,296 --> 00:23:03,132
and make sure
you're real well‐fed.

473
00:23:03,132 --> 00:23:07,636
♪

474
00:23:11,223 --> 00:23:12,641
♪ Lupin the Third ♪

475
00:23:12,641 --> 00:23:14,768
In the next episode,
Goemon loses his mojo

476
00:23:14,768 --> 00:23:17,605
when his Zantetsu sword
mysteriously disappears,

477
00:23:17,605 --> 00:23:19,940
and when Jigen and I
find it, we wish we hadn't.

478
00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:21,233
Oh, Mommy!

479
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:23,277
It's slashing through the
sky shredding a tenuous piece

480
00:23:23,277 --> 00:23:24,987
in war‐torn Central Africa.

481
00:23:24,987 --> 00:23:26,071
Tune in next time to see

482
00:23:26,071 --> 00:23:28,324
if The Yam is
Mightier Than the Sword!

483
00:23:28,324 --> 00:23:30,159
Catch ya later!

484
00:23:30,159 --> 00:24:39,728
♪

